xdrproc_t proc;
char *objp;
.fi
.ft R
.IP
Generic freeing routine. The first argument is the
.SM XDR
routine for the object being freed. The second argument
is a pointer to the object itself. Note: the pointer passed
to this routine is
.I not
freed, but what it points to
.I is
freed (recursively).
.br
